				<main id="fsPageContent" class="fsPageContent"><h1 class="fsPageTitle">Mandated Closure Information</h1>




							<div class="fsPageLayout fsLayout fsOneColumnLayout fsStyleAutoclear" id="fsEl_11856" data-use-new="true">

				<div class=" fsDiv fsStyleAutoclear" id="fsEl_11857">

				<div class="fsElement fsContent" id="fsEl_11858" data-use-new="true">

				<div class="fsElementContent">
			<p>The Southgate Community School District will be closed for the rest of this school year per the Governor's mandate. If you have any student medication(s) or essential items that you would like to pick-up, please call us at 734-246-4600 to make arrangements.   All buildings are closed. Buildings will be fully disinfected the week of March 16 - 20.  They will be disinfected again prior to students returning.</p>

<p>For information on the District's Distance Learning and COVID-19 Response Plan please access here: <a data-ally-content-id="50a6a542-aa69-46ea-83f6-485233181cdb" data-ally-file-eid="148510" data-file-name="FinalSCSDContinuityofLearningandCOVID-19ResponsePlan1.pdf" data-resource-uuid="0b7f7be8-bbed-4646-ae4d-31a7c8273a73" href="/fs/resource-manager/view/0b7f7be8-bbed-4646-ae4d-31a7c8273a73" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Continuity of Learning Plan</a>.  The plan was approved on April 14, 2020.  You can view the <a data-file-name="COLPlanApprovalLetter.pdf" data-resource-uuid="31e6b801-c63d-414c-8ef3-16768dda72aa" href="/fs/resource-manager/view/31e6b801-c63d-414c-8ef3-16768dda72aa" target="_blank">approval letter here</a>.  </p>

<p><strong>Food Offerings</strong></p>

<p>We will be offering breakfast and lunches during this closure at Davidson Middle School on Tuesdays from 11:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m.  March 17, 24 and 31. <strong>April 7 and 14 dates have now been added. </strong> Pick up only, no cafeteria dining.  <a data-file-name="Tue_Lunchpickup_fixed.pdf" href="https://www.southgateschools.com/fs/resource-manager/view/25add460-388a-40cb-a64d-8875f912005a" target="_blank">Click here for the Southgate announcement (PDF).</a>  Please click here for a <a href="https://www.resa.net/community/feeding" target="_blank">county-wide list of places</a> to receive free meals for students during the closure.  </p>

<ul>
<li>
<a data-file-name="List319.pdf" data-resource-uuid="be63dcac-dbca-4136-9322-177ca85604fb" href="/fs/resource-manager/view/be63dcac-dbca-4136-9322-177ca85604fb" target="_blank">3/19/2020 List</a> (provided by the Mayor's Office) of local restaurants still open for delivery and/or carryout</li>
	<li><a data-file-name="FoodServiceupdate3_18_20.pdf" data-resource-uuid="1d57559d-0a11-426d-9f3d-f97ba92a65a6" href="/fs/resource-manager/view/1d57559d-0a11-426d-9f3d-f97ba92a65a6" target="_blank">Memo to parents 3/18/2020</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Learning Opportunities</strong></p>

<p>We have developed learning materials for families to use at home during this closure.  The activities are grouped by grade level for lower elementary, upper elementary, middle school, and high school.  These opportunities will not be graded.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1KGigdEoGSS76d4ZUERfrx4Uv-CnN-1xhvlWGocBbskg/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">Young 5's - Grade 2</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1kG-jkmBxpAzXG7U3jsFI_0x_wk7Wqdt3nFXn3_CosUs/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">Grade 3 - 5</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ibTD73jrlZpJF5tQcmd02JG4IXBrtYB7uqJNNOUjF-Y/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">Grade 6 - 8 </a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ukDQvKrZS3nuUGe3lcZSAqXjFVoP_RcvzdbpAsPCddI/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">Grade 9 - 12</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qDA63jIWnTT1kyX4Ak8R_i2lhXaB5WASqLbuU02rWrI/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">GED / ABE and ESL</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Technology Availability</strong></p>

<p>The District is committed to providing technology on an as-needed basis to support curriculum.  At this time, we are offering chromebooks to students who receive speech services and students in grades 9 through 11.  Senior students will be offered a chromebook if needed to finish their graduation requirements.  </p>

<p>At this time, we are providing one chromebook per family.  The parent/guardian must complete this <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1Ww2N5GAGEScnk-NnCuQbIpFOKbmdhzBRszI4FDH49XE/edit" target="_blank">Chromebook Request Form</a> to receive one.  Pick up days will be April 20th and 21st.  Additional days and times may be scheduled in the future.  You will be contacted with the time and location of the pickup.   </p>

<p>By requesting a Southgate Community Schools Chromebook, you are agreeing to be responsible for the care and return of the chromebook to the District.  The chromebooks have filtering software installed, however, no filter can replace parental supervision.  The filter will be the same as what is filtered in school.  The replacements price of the Chromebook and power cord is $340.00.  It is $60.00 to replace just a power cord.  You will receive more information regarding support at the time of pickup.  The chromebook will only work when it is connected to the Internet.  The District is not responsible for providing internet access outside of the district.  </p>

<p>There are low-cost home Internet options available if you currently do not have Internet.  Please click here to <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1r9se6V5TbkkWQmPHTbRA0BwMLjrkx-B9NqRsbJS1xkc/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">download a flyer</a> with links to several providers.  </p>

<p><strong>Parent Resources</strong></p>

<p>This list has been compiled by Southgate Social Workers and Counselors to better assist our students and families during the COVID-19 crisis:  <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-occbNMh0jZgXonEt6faQSHYy3ME0N8u_NMdyMf0vms/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">Resource List for Parents</a>.</p>

<p><strong>Spirit Week March 30 </strong></p>

<p dir="ltr">Check out the videos from the March 30th district-wide Spirit Week.  You just click this link, <a data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://flipgrid.com/southgatespirit&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585662527258000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEui21fTLruwWD8rtMJeyXgu_orZw" href="https://flipgrid.com/southgatespirit" target="_blank">https://flipgrid.com/<wbr></wbr>southgatespirit</a> and you are ready to go. You can select Login using Google and choose your Southgate account. If you do not see it, you will have to enter it (students, remember that your email is your <a target="_blank">username@student.sgate.<wbr></wbr>k12.mi.us</a>).</p>

<p> We ask for your continued patience as we move through these unprecedented times.  We are in the process of working through additional learning opportunities and will share those plans in the coming days and weeks.  We will communicate any and all updates we receive related to the Southgate Community School District and your child's education.  We thank you for your understanding and patience. Our ability to come together as a community and work through these difficult times is the definition of the "Titan Pride".</p>

<p><strong>Stimulus Check Information</strong></p>

<p>Please see the link below for a Stimulus Check guide with easy to access links. This information is for those that might fall into the following categories. </p>

<p>- People who are homeless and unaccompanied youth over 18.</p>

<p>- People who have not filed taxes last year or this year.</p>

<p>*This money does not "count against" any other benefit programs. Receiving the stimulus check <b>will not </b>make you lose your SNAP,  Medicaid or other income dependent benefits. </p>

<p><span class="fs_style_26"><a href="https://mailchi.mp/5be82d507b09/how-to-get-your-1200-stimulus-check?e=5ed6460617" target="_blank">CLICK HERE FOR MORE INFORMATION </a></span></p>

<p>Thank you!</p>


